Package gw.api.financials

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BulkInvoiceItemMethods  
    CancelCheckMethods
    Customer-implementable methods for voiding and stopping checks
    CheckCreatorProvider
    Implemented by entities (currently Claim, Exposure, and CheckSet) that can return a CheckCreator, such that any new Check and Payment created by that CheckCreator will be associated with the implementing entity.
    CheckMethods  
    CheckValidationMethods
    Methods to be implemented by Checks for validating checks.
    CoverageDeductibleMethods
    Method(s) to get ClaimDeductible property on Coverage entity.
    DeductibleUnlinkMethods
    Method(s) to unlink a Deductible entity from the TransactionLineItem(s) that may be paying the deductible.
    DeleteCheckMethods  
    FinancialsCalculation
    Interface to a calculated Financial amount, such as Available Reserves or Net Total Incurred, and the transactions that contribute to that calculated amount.
    FinancialsExpression
    A building block for custom financials calculations.
    IMoney
    Represents a monetary value.
    IMutableMoney
    Represents a monetary value whose amount can be changed.
    IPairedMoney
    Represents a monetary value that has an associated monetary value.
    MoneyComponentFacade Deprecated
    Implement the IMoney, IPairedMoney, and/or IMutableMoney interfaces instead.
    PaymentMethods
    Customer-modifiable methods for payments.
    PaymentTransferMethods  
    RIFinancialsCalculation
    Interface to a calculated Financial amount based on Reinsurance (RI) transactions, such as Total Ceded Premium, and the transactions that contribute to that calculated amount.
    TransactionWizardHelper.BaseExposureListProvider  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbilityToPayResult
    Struct type class to hold the results of an abilityToPay validation when entering the New Check Wizard.
    AbstractMutablePairedMoney
    Base class for implementing a pair of money values that can be updated.
    BulkPayHelper
    This class does much of the "Behind-the-scenes" work for the Bulk Pay (i.e., Bulk Invoices) user interface.
    CheckCreator
    A class with a builder-like interface to help create Check entities and all their sub-objects.
    CheckPayeeInfo
    Parameter Object class to hold all the parameters for check payee creation.
    CheckRecurrenceCreator<T>
    An abstract superclass of MonthlyCheckRecurrenceCreator and WeeklyCheckRecurrenceCreator, which help create CheckRecurrence entities for use with CheckCreator.
    CheckUtil
    Provides static methods for working with checks throughout the ClaimCenter user interface.
    CheckWizardInfoBase
    This class stores wizard-scoped information for the NewCheckWizard, such as the check currently being edited and other session specific information.
    ClaimFinancialsTransactionsOption
    Represents the filtering options used on the ClaimFinancialsTransactions page.
    ClaimFinancialsTransactionsOption.CustomOption
    Implements the special Custom option, which allows all transaction types but restricts the transactions to just those whose ids are specified in a given list, stored in the user's session.
    ClaimFinancialsTransactionsUtil
    ISymbol source for the Transactions LV and LVs of subtypes (e.g., Payment, Reserve, etc), and for ChecksLV.
    CurrencyAmount
    Represents a monetary amount with a currency.
    CurrencyAmountPair
    Represents the same amount of money in two currencies.
    FinancialsCalculations
    Provides instances of FinacialsCalculation that represent a particular Financials calculated amount, such as Available Reserves or Net Total Incurred.
    FinancialsCalculationUtil
    Provides instances of FinacialsCalculation that represent a particular Financials calculated amount, such as Available Reserves or Net Total Incurred.
    FinancialsCalculator<C extends FinancialsCalculator>
    A FinancialsCalculator contains information on how a financials calculation can be made.
    FinancialsCalculatorWithReservingAmount
    A FinancialsCalculatorWithReservingAmount is and extension (subclass) of a FinancialsCalculator which additionally lets the caller ask for the ReservingAmount.
    FinancialsUtil
    Provides methods for manipulating transactions in the ClaimCenter user inteface.
    FloatingFinancialsCalculations
    Static factory class for FinancialsCalculators that use Floating Financials behavior When evaluating reserving amounts, they are converted into the claim currency using current market rates.
    KeyableBeanReloader
    This class handles the work of evicting a keyable bean from its current bundle and reloading it to get the latest version while being sure not to lose any changes in the current bundle.
    MoneyComponentFacadeHelper Deprecated
    Since MoneyComponentFacade is deprecated.
    MonthlyCheckRecurrenceCreator
    Helps create a MonthlyCheckRecurrence, for use with CheckCreator.
    RecoveryReserveWizardHelper
    This class provides helpful methods for the NewRecoveryReserveSet page.
    ReserveWizardHelper
    This class provides helpful methods for the NewReserveSet page.
    ReserveZeroingBundleCommitHandler
    Class description...
    TransactionFinderStandard
    Class description...
    TransactionSetLinkDocumentHelper
    Toolbar button which allows the user to pick a document to link to a transaction set.
    TransactionWizardHelper
    Parent class of the ReserveWizardHelper and RecoveryReserveWizardHelper.
    WeeklyCheckRecurrenceCreator
    Helps create a WeeklyCheckRecurrence, for use with CheckCreator.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CloseValidationException
    Subclass of WorkflowValidationException used only when a validation error occurs while closing an object; some callers may want to handle such validation errors specially
    PaymentExceedsReservesException
    This exception is thrown when the sum of the payments exceeds the available reserves.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    CurrencyProperty
    Annotation used by CurrencyAmountComponent to specify the name of the currency property.
    ExchangeRateProperty
    Annotation used by CurrencyAmountComponent to specify the name of the exchange rate property, to be used to calculate conversions between the primary and secondary currencies.
    SecondaryMoneyComponent
    Annotation used by CurrencyAmountComponent to specify the name of the secondary amount property, if any.
